{
  "doc_id": "34627",
  "text": "Previous research [CITATION_1] presents a mixed picture of the doctor's involvement, with some patients reporting disinterest by doctors when discussing the practice of HBPM. This creates reluctance to seek further medical advice, especially when home monitoring is self-initiated without a medical prompt [CITATION_2] . Evidence also suggests that healthcare professionals are concerned that their workload may increase as patients become unnecessarily over-preoccupied with such measurements [CITATION_3] . Interestingly, this is in contrast to patients' views who believe that HBPM helps them visit the doctor less often and avoid 'bothering' him/her [CITATION_4] .",
